	<h2>Art From the Heart 2026 Presents: A Ballet Fiesta and Dance of the Coralines</h2><span><br/></span>A Ballet Fiesta: Join the Heart ballet dancers in the re-telling of two classic stories; Don Quixote and Paquita. Dancers from Saturday Ballet 1 to Adult Ballet class join our pre professionals under the direction of Sachi Kambara to entertain you and take your breath away with this magical and stunning glimpse into two favourite ballets.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Dance of the Coralines: An original piece written by Amy Rutherford, Dance of the Coralines features our 6 graduating Fly dancers as quirky, whimsical and outlandish characters. Performed by the Heart’s Pre Professional classes, with a prologue by Beat Street 4 and 5, Dance of the Coralines is bound to be a memorable experience, with incredible dance numbers choreographed by visiting choreographers Melanie DeMalo and Lady C, and costumes designed and built by the talented Chantal LaFreniere.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Art From the Heart 2026, Presented by Gilday Holdings Ltd, Quantum Machine Works Ltd. and Streamline Architects.<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>This year’s Art From the Heart is made-up of four different performances: <span><br/></span>Dance of the Coralines (an original piece by our Pre Professionals, including Beat Street 4, 5)<span><br/></span>A Ballet Fiesta (all Ballet)<span><br/></span>I Love You So Munsch (Recreational and After School Crews 1, 2 & 3 levels)<span><br/></span>Annie JR.(Musical Theatre and Classical Squad 4, 5).<span><br/></span><span><br/></span>Please ensure your tickets correspond to the shows you are intending on seeing!<span><br/></span>
